UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Donnie Jermaine LEWIS, also known as D-Lew, Defendant-Appellant. No. 06-30273

Summary Calendar,

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. April 9, 2008. Camffle Ann Domingue, Assistant U.S. Attorney) u s. Attor^s office, Western District of Louisiana; Lafayette, LA, for p]ajntiff_Ap ellee Christopher Albert Aberle, Mandeville, LA, for Defendant-Appellant,

Before DAVIS, BARKSDALE, and BENAVIDES, Circuit Judges.

*318 ON REMAND FROM THE SUPREME COURT OF THE UNITED STATES

PER CURIAM: *

Donnie Jermaine Lewis’ sentence is VACATED and this matter is REMANDED to district court for resentencing in the light of Kimbrough v. United States, — U.S.-, 128 S.Ct. 558, 169 L.Ed.2d 481 (2007).

SENTENCE VACATED; REMANDED

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
